Johnson Controls Inc. said it formed a joint venture with Yokogawa Electric Corp. of Tokyo to make and market process-control instruments and install and service automation equipment in North America. 

Johnson, a Milwaukee-based maker of building-control systems, said the new venture will be called Johnson Yokogawa Corp. and is expected to be completed by January.
Yokogawa makes industrial process-control systems. 

The two companies said they expect annual sales for the joint venture to be about $200 million. 

